  "prompt": "Is it ok to spend the night with my fianc\u00e9 or does it go against God?",
  "response": "The question of whether it's okay to spend the night with your fianc\u00e9 varies greatly depending on individual beliefs, cultural norms, and religious interpretations. Many religious traditions emphasize the importance of abstaining from sex until marriage, viewing cohabitation or spending the night together as potentially compromising spiritual or moral values. \n\nHowever, in modern contexts, many couples choose to spend nights together before marriage, emphasizing trust, commitment, and the practical aspects of their relationship. \n\nIt's essential to consider your own beliefs, values, and the teachings of your faith tradition. Having an open and honest discussion with your fianc\u00e9 about your views on this can also help you both make a decision that aligns with your values. Ultimately, what matters most is mutual respect, understanding, and alignment with your personal beliefs.",
